{{Han etym}}
{{liushu|p}} – a standing person. A radical form of {{m|zh|人}}.

Also {{Han simp|兒|f=臼|t=&nbsp;|nocap=y}}.

* It may be used to specially write erhua (or the rhotic sound) in traditional Chinese, in contrast with {{zh-l|兒|[[child]]}}.
** {{quote-book|lang=zh|year=1950|author={{w2|zh|林漢達|林濤}} (Lin Tao)|title={{lang|zh|定型化新文字}} (Dingshinghua Sin Wenz)|trans-title=|publisher={{w2|zh|生活·讀書·新知三聯書店}}|edition=2nd|page=}}
**: {{quote|zh|有人把拉丁化新文字的方案跟寫法看做神聖不可侵犯的東西，不准有[[一點兒|一點儿]]改變{{...}}|There are some who believe that the Latinxua Sin Wenz scheme and spelling are sacred things that should not be violated, and that there must not be even the tiniest bit of change{{...}}}}
**: {{quote|zh|r念“儿”只有“[[兒]]”“二”“而”這幾個字{{...}}|When ''r'' is read as {{lang|zh|儿}}, the only candidates are "child", "two", and "and"{{...}}}}
* When used to represent ''[[erhua]]'', it may be subscript.
** {{quote-book|lang=zh|year=1968|author={{w2|zh|趙元任}} ({{w|Yuen Ren Chao}})|title={{lang|zh|語言問題}}|trans-title=Problems in Linguistics|publisher={{w2|zh|臺灣商務印書館}}|page=83}}
**: {{quote|zh|固然平常念一個單字的時候，重音的音節在樂音上也是高[[一點兒|一點<sub>儿</sub>]]，不過它不一定老是這個樣子。|Admittedly, when pronouncing these a word, the stressed syllable is, musically speaking, a bit higher-pitched, but this is not necessarily always the case.}}
